                        <h1><a name="17016"></a><a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=17016">Reach The Beach</a></h1>
                        <div class="ItemInfo">[<a href="/blogs/selectBlog.html?id=2733&amp;articleId=17016" alt="Use this to refer to the specific blog entry">URL</a>] Posted on 15 June 2004 14:31,  <a href="/blogs/readMore.html?id=17016">2 comments in 1 threads.</a> Last comment on 16 June 2004 13:51.
                        </div>
                        <div>Well, that was a lovely little interlude. Now, back into the real world of Earthdawn. I am currently working on the Player's
                           Compendium. Once we get the next build up for peer review, I am hoping to get this out to the playtesters so it can be disseminated,
                           pulled apart, mauled, critiqued and generally used by some hardcore Earthdawn gamers.
                           
                           <p>Down here in New Zealand we have an advert for cheese with a slogan "good things take time" -- well, at the risk of comparing
                              this book (and the others) to a block of aged cheddar, we hope this is the case. You are all being, I must say, incredibly
                              patient with us. We take that trust seriously and hope we don't disappoint!
                           </p>
                           
                           <p>Back to the coal-face now, keyboard under arm and kicking the mouse as I go... More bloggy goodness tomorrow.</p>
                           
                           <p>Take kaer, J;)</p>
                           
                           <p>PS: 10 points to the person who can Name the band for which this posting is titled!</p>
                        </div><br></td>
